<https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/royal-air-force-museum> <http://ogp.me/ns#description> "The Royal Air Force Museum (RAFM) tells the story of British aviation, from early bi-planes to the latest strike-jets. It is based on two sites - Colindale in North London, and Cosford in Shropshire, and is free to visit. RAFM is an executive non-departmental public body, sponsored by the Ministry of Defence ."@en .
